              overview: 'An idempotent transform produces the same output regardless of how many times it runs on the same input. For SQL transforms: use INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING or MERGE with a deterministic key. For file outputs: write to a content-addressed path (s3://features/{date}/{hash}/). CDC (Change Data Capture) captures row-level database changes as an event stream — tools: Debezium (Postgres WAL), Kafka Connect, AWS DMS. Incremental feature updates process only changed rows since the last watermark, reducing featurization time from hours to minutes.',
